Uses of Interface
javaslang.collection.JSeq

  • Packages that use JSeq 
    Package Description
    javaslang.collection
    Immutable collections based on JTraversable like the linked list JList and the lazy linked list JStream.

    • Uses of JSeq in javaslang.collection

      Subinterfaces of JSeq in javaslang.collection 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  JList<T>
      A JList is an eager sequence of elements.
      interface  JStream<T>
      A JStream is lazy sequence of elements which may be infinitely long.
      Classes in javaslang.collection that implement JSeq 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  JList.AbstractList<T>
      This class is needed because the interface JList cannot use default methods to override Object's non-final methods equals, hashCode and toString.
      static class  JList.Cons<T>
      Non-empty JList, consisting of a head and a tail.
      static class  JList.Nil<T>
      Representation of the singleton empty JList.
      static class  JStream.AbstractStream<T>
      This class is needed because the interface JStream cannot use default methods to override Object's non-final methods equals, hashCode and toString.
      static class  JStream.Cons<T>
      Non-empty JStream, consisting of a head, a tail and an optional AutoCloseable.
      static class  JStream.Nil<T>
      The empty JStream.
